{"source_key":"sha256-564e11a209e70e03f16b9e715ff8b50f","record_index":2535,"record_hash":"sha256:5c4184c9e673825f57c48e9592eb61bf3a36bc62e9bcd8ac8f4e08f8b2b74708","timestamp":"2026-05-20T17:59:29.598Z","kind":"message","source_event_kind":"codex:response_item:message","role":"user","text":"<subagent_notification>\n{\"agent_path\":\"[REDACTED:entropy]\",\"status\":{\"completed\":\"Findings:\\n\\n- **Fix now:** public timeline/detail reads drop the environment evidence they just stored. `TurnDetail` persists `observed_targets` and `environment` in [write.rs](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/gitmeta/write.rs:168), but `TimelineTurn` only exposes `environment_snapshot_status` and `records` in [read.rs](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/gitmeta/read.rs:27), and `StoredTurnDetail` deserializes only `records` in [mod.rs](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/gitmeta/mod.rs:82). That forces review/handoff consumers to know GitMeta internals to get the actual turn context. Expose a typed turn detail projection, or include environment/observed targets on timeline/detail turns.\\n\\n- **Fix now:** `RelatedTarget` leaks private key grammar into the public API. Callers must know to pass strings like `ref:refs/heads/main`, `gitbutler-review:<id>`, or `gitbutler-change:<id>` from [read.rs](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/gitmeta/read.rs:43), matching constructors buried in [environment.rs](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/environment.rs:274) and [environment.rs](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/environment.rs:313). A caller passing `main`, PR number, or change id gets silent misses. Add public constructors/newtypes that build canonical observation keys inside `but-agentlog`.\\n\\n- **Document:** `find_related_sessions` sorts by related turn count in [read.rs](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/gitmeta/read.rs:231). That is basically ranking policy, while the design says scoring belongs above primitives. Either document “count-desc evidence order” as the primitive contract, or make it boring deterministic ordering and leave ranking to consumers.\\n\\nNo boundary panic on CLI/capture/transcript/gitmeta/redaction otherwise. CLI stays thin, transcript parsing does not know GitMeta, redaction is localized, and environment capture is a repo-local adapter. Validation passed: `cargo check -p but-agentlog --all-targets` and `cargo test -p but-agentlog`.\"}}\n</subagent_notification>","tool_name":null,"tool_input":null,"source_record":{"timestamp":"2026-05-20T17:59:29.598Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"message","role":"user"}}}